LIBERTY UTILITIES (GRANITE STATE ELECTRIC) CORP.
Market-Based Sales Tariff
1. Availability. Liberty Utilities (Granite State Electric) Corp. ("Liberty Utilities") shall make available from time to time electric energy and/or capacity for sale under this Tariff. The sale of electric energy and/or capacity shall be made at Liberty Utilities' sole discretion.
2. Applicability. This Tariff is applicable to all FERC-jurisdictional sales of electric energy or capacity by Liberty Utilities not otherwise subject to a particular Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("FERC" or the "Commission") rate schedule or tariff of Liberty Utilities.
3. Rates. All sales under this Tariff shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Liberty Utilities or established pursuant to market rules or tariff provisions accepted by the FERC.
4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Liberty Utilities.
5. Effective Date. This Tariff is effective on the date authorized by FERC.
6. Changes in Rates, Terms and Conditions. Nothing herein affects the right of Liberty Utilities to unilaterally make application to the FERC for a change of rates, terms or conditions of this Tariff pursuant to Section 205 of the Federal Power Act and regulations thereunder.
7. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Liberty Utilities shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Liberty Utilities' market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Liberty Utilities to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Liberty Utilities' market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Liberty Utilities' market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff.
8. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. N/A
9. Seller Category. Liberty Utilities is a Category 2 seller in the Northeast region, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a). Liberty Utilities is a Category 1 seller in the Central, Northwest, Southeast, Southwest, and Southwest Power Pool regions, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
